AmazonSmile is a way for customers to support their favorite charitable organization every time they shop with Amazon.

Shoppers who start at smile.amazon.com will find the same Amazon they know and love, with the added bonus that Amazon will donate a portion of the price of eligible purchases to the charity of your choice.

Signing up is easy!

Here's how to shop AmazonSmile:

1. Visit smile.amazon.com

2. Sign in with your Amazon.com credentials

3. Choose a charitable organization to receive donations, or search for the charity of your choice

4. Select your charity. Please select Thomas Edison Charter School.

4. Start shopping!

We apologize for so much confusion and appreciate your patience as we navigate this new school year with its many challenges.

Today, the requirements for face coverings in schools was updated by the state of Utah.

Face shields are no longer an acceptable face covering for students to wear during school.

Please help us follow this regulation by providing your student(s) with face masks. If you have concerns regarding this new requirement please contact Mrs. Kirk at the front office.

post_text: Parents, as the beginning of school approaches, please make sure your students are aware of the dangers of playing on/in these lids and grates. We have some students who use this area to walk to and from school. The safety of our students is our top priority. Nibley, Utah
shared_text:
Nibley, Utah
July 30 at 12:45 PM ·

Parents PLEASE work with your children to help them understand that beyond these storm-water lids and grates there are DANGEROUS and even DEADLY things. There have been some clever children that have figured out how to get past these and are playing inside our storm-water system. We are particularly concerned about drains and grates at the disc golf course on 1200 West (Sunrise Meadows/Discovery Park) where this is happening. Thank you parents for doing all you can to keep your children safe.

POTION MASTERS CONTEST DETAILS:

Here is your chance to win an autographed copy of POTION MASTERS by Frank L. Cole from Shadow Mountain Publishing

DISCLAIMER: This contest will require creativity and imagination.

To enter, create a video of you describing the potion you would like to create.
Be creative! Include the ingredients and what the potion does. Don't forget to name your potion!
Costumes and theatrics are encouraged. Most importantly, have fun with it.

To submit, upload your video to your Facebook page or your YouTube channel using the hashtag #TECSPotions. Remember to make your video public and to tag the school in your post so we can see it!

Deadline is Friday, April 24th.
The winner will be chosen randomly from the submissions and announced on Facebook and Instagram.

post_text: A special day of service from TECS south 'One Voice' choir students as they performed a 30 min. program to 5 assisted care centers in the valley. Ate lunch on the army truck and enjoyed Aggie Ice Cream! The army truck was a big hit and even with its bumpy rockous ride the students loved it. It was a totally wonderful day full of tears, laughter, love and of course gratitude for our freedom and the sacrifice of so many! #tecssouth #tecsonevoice

shared_text:
Michelle Labrum Loveland is with Neal Loveland at Thomas Edison Charter School South.
May 23, 2019 at 11:13 PM · Nibley, UT ·

I've been sad these last few weeks knowing that Hayden doesn't want to "Walk" for graduation. It took me a few days to really figure out why it was bugging me so much.. I needed to be able to celebrate her accomplishment... well today I had that opportunity. Thomas Edison Charter School invited all graduating seniors that had attended TECS earlier to come do a "Senior Walk" Where they were able to walk the halls and be cheered by all the younger students, visit with past teachers and take a few photos. I was able to CELEBRATE my beautiful daughter. Yep I was a crying baby.

post_text:
Dear 2019 High School Graduates,

We are so excited and proud of you! We would like to honor you at our “2019 Grad Walk”. If you spent ANY of your years at Thomas Edison we would like to invite you to walk our halls one last time. Please meet in the foyer at 2:40 on Thursday, May 23rd. The walk will begin promptly at 2:45. If you have your cap and gown please bring them. Our students can’t wait to cheer for you and your former teachers will be thrilled to see you again.

P.S. Please help us spread the word to your classmates that we may not have had an email for. It should be a fun reunion.

post_text:
Throughout the next couple of weeks, Thomas Edison Charter School will be supporting the Food Pantry by holding our annual canned food drive.

We will begin taking donations on Monday, November 5th, and we will continue to do so until Tuesday, November 20th. Donations should be brought to each student's individual classes.

We ask that donations be non-perishable items, such as cans of food, cake mixes, cereal, etc. Please do not donate items that have previously been opened or that are expired. This is a great cause and the extra food goes a long way this time of the year.

Thank you in advance for your help and support!
text:
Throughout the next couple of weeks, Thomas Edison Charter School will be supporting the Food Pantry by holding our annual canned food drive.

We will begin taking donations on Monday, November 5th, and we will continue to do so until Tuesday, November 20th. Donations should be brought to each student's individual classes.

We ask that donations be non-perishable items, such as cans of food, cake mixes, cereal, etc. Please do not donate items that have previously been opened or that are expired. This is a great cause and the extra food goes a long way this time of the year.

Thank you in advance for your help and support!

Student Openings

Thomas Edison South has limited spaces still available in Kindergarten through 8th grade for the upcoming 2018-19 school year. Please share your TECS experience with friends and family whose children would thrive in our challenging and high-expectation program.

For more information, please contact the school at 435-752-0123. Invite them to come in to visit our school and speak with an administrator.

Exciting news from the National History Day competition. Two TECS South students were recognized for their projects. Caitlin Tran Radovan placed 4th in the Junior division nationally for individual website. She also received the "Best of State" Junior division in all categories for the state of Utah. Gracyn Killpack also received an Honorable Mention. We are so proud of the hard work and dedication our students put into their projects. They all did amazing work! #nationalhistoryday #tecssouth

post_text: The Fourth Annual Biggest Writer Challenge is officially underway! With 100 student participants and a couple dozen staff, parents, and TECS alumni, each individual's quest to write a 10,000 word story in a month has kicked off with a bang. Mr. Cureton even hosts a classroom full of eager students during lunch each day who'd rather write than most anything else. Our goal to eclipse 1,000,000 words is sure to be reached with these leaders at the helm. Let's Go The Distance!
